      "rationale": "Thirteen model inputs catalogued. Distributions assigned to inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and blood viscosity based on experimental measurements. Remaining inputs treated as deterministic with documented values and sources. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo through surrogate model; 95th-percentile NIH remains below threshold. A screening sensitivity study was verbally discussed during the credibility review to identify the most influential inputs, confirming impeller tip speed as the dominant driver of NIH variability; these findings are summarized in the UQ narrative above."
