    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cv-sim-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Uncertainty quantification demonstrates that the 95th-percentile NIH remains below the RH < 1 acceptance criterion under all sampled boundary condition combinations. A screening sensitivity study discussed during review supports the conclusion that impeller tip speed is the dominant driver; this finding is consistent with physical expectations and increases confidence in the UQ conclusions. The model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
